<item>
            <title>[DATAREDIS-124] SubscriptionTask doesn&apos;t release JedisConnection and causing future SubscriptionTasks to block</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREDIS-124</link>
                <project id="10604" key="DATAREDIS">Spring Data Redis</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In RedisMessageListenerContainer.SubscriptionTask class, the run() function gets a new JedisConnection from the underlying Jedis pool (assuming using Jedis) but after the subscription ends it doesn&apos;t return the connection back to the pool, causing future subscriptionTask to block on getConnection().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce the bug:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Create a RedisMessageListenerContainer based on a Jedis pool. &lt;br/&gt;
2. Call addListener on the container.&lt;br/&gt;
3. Call RemoveListener to remove the subscribed listener.&lt;br/&gt;
repeat 2 and 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once the pool is exhausted, the future subscription task will block for ever.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
